563
00:38:49,670 --> 00:38:52,290
You're so bad at catching these things.

564
00:38:52,290 --> 00:38:56,920
I bought drinks only for you and waited for you whenever you stayed late.

565
00:38:56,920 --> 00:39:03,350
I thought you found me comfortable.

566
00:39:03,350 --> 00:39:06,040
So, on that note...

567
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:10,420
Dan Dan, would you like to go out with me?

568
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:17,080
I'm sorry.

569
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:22,600
I like someone else.

570
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:25,320
Is it the Chairman from earlier?

571
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:29,090
I knew it.

572
00:39:29,090 --> 00:39:32,470
That's why I'm telling you now.

573
00:39:32,470 --> 00:39:37,180
That Chairman and you don't fit together.

574
00:39:37,180 --> 00:39:40,680
And that Chairman has another woman.

575
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,240
Sunbae.

576
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:48,120
I don't know what makes you say the Chairman and I don't fit together,

577
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:52,040
but I liked him, and I still haven't gotten over him.

578
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:57,520
I don't think it's right to accept you when I have feelings for someone else.

579
00:39:57,520 --> 00:40:01,880
I would like to keep our relationship as it is.

580
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:04,470
- Dan Dan–
- I'm really sorry.

581
00:40:04,470 --> 00:40:06,650
I'll get going first.

582
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:52,910
Chairman, thank you for coming out so late.

583
00:40:52,910 --> 00:40:57,420
Ms. Park, what is it that you have to ask me?

584
00:40:57,450 --> 00:41:01,630
Chairman, who was that woman from today?

585
00:41:01,630 --> 00:41:03,520
What is her relationship with you?

586
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:07,180
What relationship do you have with her where she can link arms with you?

587
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,400
Why do you need to know?

588
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:14,780
Chairman, why are you letting anyone hold arms with you?

589
00:41:14,780 --> 00:41:18,220
Who is that woman?

590
00:41:18,260 --> 00:41:23,410
It's not just anyone. She's someone that I'm dating.

591
00:41:26,530 --> 00:41:29,760
Someone you're dating?

592
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,360
Yes.

593
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:35,400
We are similar in age and have a similar background.

594
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:38,420
So I'm planning to get into a serious relationship with her.

595
00:41:38,420 --> 00:41:45,000
So I hope you meet someone that fits you too.

596
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:49,430
Chairman, what are you talking about right now?

597
00:41:49,430 --> 00:41:55,000
You're going out with her because you're similar in age and have a similar background?

598
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:58,730
Not because you like her?

599
00:41:58,730 --> 00:42:04,220
I said no to someone who said they liked me because

600
00:42:04,220 --> 00:42:08,100
I still like you.

601
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:15,110
It's not right for them to meet a new person when you like someone else.

602
00:42:17,360 --> 00:42:21,090
So are you here to say this?

603
00:42:21,090 --> 00:42:22,740
Yes.

604
00:42:22,740 --> 00:42:26,180
Chairman, you're trying to get closure with me

605
00:42:26,180 --> 00:42:30,930
and get rid of me by meeting another woman, aren't you?

606
00:42:30,930 --> 00:42:34,880
I'll be straightforward. That's wrong.

607
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:38,070
Meeting another woman when you still like me

608
00:42:38,070 --> 00:42:41,000
is not something you should do to that woman.

609
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,080
- Ms. Park–
- Go ahead,

610
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:46,170
say whatever you need to say.

611
00:42:46,170 --> 00:42:49,000
I handle my own business.

612
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,540
You seem to have said everything you needed to.

613
00:42:51,540 --> 00:42:55,900
I'm going to head in now. Go home safely.

614
00:42:57,480 --> 00:42:59,860
Chairman, I'm telling you,

615
00:42:59,860 --> 00:43:03,390
it won't work out with her because you like me!

616
00:43:03,390 --> 00:43:06,690
You'll see I'm right!

617
00:43:22,510 --> 00:43:27,750
Those damn people... Were they lying to me the whole time?

618
00:43:31,460 --> 00:43:34,350
[Tasty 60th Chicken]

619
00:43:34,350 --> 00:43:38,430
In-law. When did you find out about this?

620
00:43:38,430 --> 00:43:41,300
How could you leave me out when you all knew about it?

621
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:43,510
So were you going to lie to me

622
00:43:43,510 --> 00:43:46,750
and make Joon Oh your son-in-law?

623
00:43:46,750 --> 00:43:49,580
Sister-in-law, was that the plan?

624
00:43:49,580 --> 00:43:51,540
No, no.

625
00:43:51,540 --> 00:43:54,310
I told you, we found out yesterday too.

626
00:43:54,310 --> 00:43:58,200
You should've told me then. Why didn't you tell me right away?

627
00:43:58,200 --> 00:44:00,910
We were trying to make them split up before you found out.

628
00:44:00,910 --> 00:44:05,230
But then Joon Oh said he couldn't break up with her at all. So what could we have done?

629
00:44:05,230 --> 00:44:10,220
And Joon Oh said that extended in-laws can legally get married.

630
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,250
What?

631
00:44:12,250 --> 00:44:15,000
- Did my Joon Oh say that?
- Yes.

632
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,930
My mom and I heard it together.

633
00:44:17,930 --> 00:44:22,010
I won't accept them.

634
00:44:22,010 --> 00:44:24,440
Of course.

635
00:44:24,440 --> 00:44:27,410
It doesn't make sense. We don't accept it either.

636
00:44:27,410 --> 00:44:30,190
How could in-laws become in-laws?

637
00:44:30,190 --> 00:44:33,600
- I'm totally against it.
- Yes, Sister-in-law.

638
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:35,610
Please, persuade Joon Oh,

639
00:44:35,610 --> 00:44:39,700
and stop him from dating Mi Rim.

640
00:44:39,730 --> 00:44:41,830
Okay.

641
00:44:41,830 --> 00:44:44,580
Well, I should.

642
00:44:44,580 --> 00:44:46,410
What did I just hear?

643
00:44:46,410 --> 00:44:48,400
What's this about Joon Oh and Mi Rim?

644
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:51,690
Soo Chul, you didn't know either.

645
00:44:51,690 --> 00:44:55,670
Soo Chul, what are we going to do?

646
00:44:55,670 --> 00:44:59,890
Mi Rim and Joon Oh were living together behind our backs.

647
00:44:59,890 --> 00:45:01,780
What?

648
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:04,340
Were they living together?

649
00:45:18,010 --> 00:45:20,890
Hyung. I don't know what it is,

650
00:45:20,890 --> 00:45:23,700
but I think something's happening over there again.

651
00:45:23,700 --> 00:45:26,480
It looks serious.

652
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:29,390
You're right. I wonder what's up.

653
00:45:29,390 --> 00:45:32,140
I don't think that family is good.

654
00:45:32,140 --> 00:45:35,920
I thought Dan Dan was good for Hyun Bin because I adore her,

655
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:37,930
but I'm concerned.

656
00:45:37,930 --> 00:45:41,710
It seems like something happens in that family every day.

657
00:45:41,710 --> 00:45:44,240
If Hyun Bin marries that family,

658
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:46,930
he won't survive a day.

659
00:45:48,350 --> 00:45:51,050
Why do you worry about their household?

660
00:45:51,050 --> 00:45:54,150
We can just bring Dan Dan.

661
00:45:54,150 --> 00:45:57,810
You worry too much.

662
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:07,290
Joon Oh and Mi Rim,

663
00:46:07,290 --> 00:46:10,290
what were you thinking? Living together without letting the adults know.

664
00:46:10,290 --> 00:46:14,560
Joon Oh, you tell me. What are you planning to do?

665
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:20,700
We were dating before my mom and you found each other.

666
00:46:20,700 --> 00:46:22,970
We don't think it was wrong for us to have lived together.

667
00:46:22,970 --> 00:46:26,010
- You little punk!
- Noona, stop.

668
00:46:27,620 --> 00:46:32,650
What's wrong with living with someone you like? Living with someone you don't like is wrong.

669
00:46:32,650 --> 00:46:34,410
We didn't do anything wrong.

670
00:46:34,410 --> 00:46:39,220
I'm going to keep dating Mi Rim.

671
00:46:39,220 --> 00:46:42,610
So stop telling us what to do based on the adult's standards.

672
00:46:42,610 --> 00:46:49,590
I'm all grown up, and I'm at an age where I can live independently without parental agreement and even marry.

673
00:46:49,590 --> 00:46:52,340
Are you saying you did a great job?

674
00:46:52,340 --> 00:46:54,480
You're not even dry behind the ears,

675
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:57,330
and how dare you live together!?

676
00:46:57,330 --> 00:47:01,760
Mom, we were there for each other when we were suffering.

677
00:47:01,760 --> 00:47:04,270
So don't speak of us so easily.

678
00:47:04,270 --> 00:47:11,190
And you don't have the right to judge us even if you're family and adults.

679
00:47:11,190 --> 00:47:14,230
- Let's go, Mi Rim.
- What? Hey!

680
00:47:14,230 --> 00:47:17,290
- Joon Oh!
- We'll get going.

681
00:47:17,290 --> 00:47:20,020
- Hey! Joon Oh!
- Mi Rim!

682
00:47:20,020 --> 00:47:22,760
What do we even...

683
00:47:24,390 --> 00:47:26,880
Oh, my goodness...

684
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:30,940
I mean, Soo Chul, why is Joon Oh acting like this?

685
00:47:30,940 --> 00:47:32,820
He's not that kind of person.

686
00:47:32,820 --> 00:47:35,710
Oh my, now that I saw that,

687
00:47:35,710 --> 00:47:39,640
I can see that Joon Oh was the one that lured Mi Rim.

688
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:42,320
What's going to happen to Mi Rim?

689
00:47:42,320 --> 00:47:44,610
After all that happened,

690
00:47:44,610 --> 00:47:47,770
shouldn't Joon Oh be responsible for Mi Rim?

691
00:47:47,770 --> 00:47:51,610
In-law, what do you mean he should be responsible?

692
00:47:51,610 --> 00:47:54,370
How could you say that in modern times?

693
00:47:54,370 --> 00:47:57,850
It's not the Joseon dynasty or something.

694
00:47:57,850 --> 00:48:02,720
I mean, the man must take responsibility just because they lived together?

695
00:48:02,720 --> 00:48:07,030
- That's nonsense!
- It's not nonsense!

696
00:48:07,030 --> 00:48:10,660
Joon Oh ruined our Mi Rim's future marriage!

697
00:48:10,660 --> 00:48:12,640
And they're living together right now.

698
00:48:12,640 --> 00:48:16,280
Shouldn't they get a marriage registration as soon as possible?

699
00:48:16,280 --> 00:48:18,150
Oh, my goodness!

700
00:48:18,150 --> 00:48:20,640
Marriage registration!?

701
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:24,240
How could you say such a terrible thing!

702
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:30,480
Do you think I raised Joon Oh so preciously just to give him to that kind of girl?

703
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:34,700
Joon Oh is a medical student.

704
00:48:34,700 --> 00:48:39,700
You needed to bring three keys back in the day if you wanted a doctor as your son-in-law.

705
00:48:39,700 --> 00:48:44,000
How dare you think of snatching him up?

706
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:48,100
My goodness, how could you talk this way?

707
00:48:48,100 --> 00:48:54,040
- Mom...
- Our Mi Rim is also a precious granddaughter to me.

708
00:48:54,040 --> 00:48:57,110
How could you say that?

709
00:48:57,110 --> 00:49:02,180
Our Mi Rim lost both her parents on the same day and time to a car accident...

710
00:49:02,180 --> 00:49:04,520
She's a poor child...

711
00:49:04,520 --> 00:49:07,020
Don't be like this to her.

712
00:49:07,020 --> 00:49:11,800
Do you know how kind Mi Rim is?

713
00:49:11,800 --> 00:49:15,040
I wasn't able to raise her as precious as you did with your son,

714
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:19,320
but she's a precious granddaughter that I raised with my love.

715
00:49:19,320 --> 00:49:23,150
Oh my, oh my...

716
00:49:23,150 --> 00:49:25,960
What is all this?

717
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:29,930
Soo Chul, what is all this?

718
00:49:29,930 --> 00:49:34,360
How can you and I become in-laws?

719
00:49:34,360 --> 00:49:40,820
I was fixing up next door to let you move in.

720
00:49:40,820 --> 00:49:43,720
I really...

721
00:49:43,720 --> 00:49:46,840
I don't think I can see you for a while.

722
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:49,700
Oh really, what is all this!?

723
00:49:49,700 --> 00:49:51,850
Noona. Noona!

724
00:49:51,850 --> 00:49:55,600
- Noona! Noona!
- Older-sister-in-law...

725
00:49:55,600 --> 00:49:57,800
- Noona!
- Mom,

726
00:49:57,800 --> 00:50:00,760
what did she just say? She's fixing up next door?

727
00:50:00,760 --> 00:50:02,590
What do we do?

728
00:50:02,590 --> 00:50:04,350
It's all because of Mi Rim.

729
00:50:04,350 --> 00:50:07,810
Now we can't live in her house!

730
00:50:07,810 --> 00:50:11,770
You idiot! That's not the problem right now!

731
00:50:11,770 --> 00:50:14,750
She's looking down on Mi Rim like that!

732
00:50:14,750 --> 00:50:18,000
I can't allow this!

733
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:20,810
My goodness...

734
00:50:37,660 --> 00:50:40,650
Why didn't Ms. Yeoju fry some meat?

735
00:50:40,650 --> 00:50:43,260
So annoying.

736
00:50:59,080 --> 00:51:02,480
I thought I was going to starve to death.

737
00:51:08,030 --> 00:51:10,740
This is so good.

738
00:51:32,310 --> 00:51:34,350
What's this?

739
00:51:35,780 --> 00:51:39,340
Did someone make bibimbap last night and eat it?

740
00:51:39,340 --> 00:51:44,320
Wait, there's no one who'd eat this kind of bibimbap in this house.

741
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:46,070
That's weird.

742
00:51:46,070 --> 00:51:50,130
Who ate this so cleanly?

743
00:51:52,600 --> 00:51:54,160
Good morning.

744
00:51:54,160 --> 00:51:57,300
Yes, Chairman. Good morning.

745
00:52:00,070 --> 00:52:01,850
Chairman,

746
00:52:01,850 --> 00:52:06,470
did you eat bibimbap last night by any chance?

747
00:52:06,470 --> 00:52:08,380
Excuse me?

748
00:52:08,380 --> 00:52:10,780
N-n-no, it's nothing.

749
00:52:10,780 --> 00:52:13,890
Chairman would never do that.

750
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:23,330
Oh, right. Last time Jenny and Se Chan said they went to Ms. Park's house

751
00:52:23,330 --> 00:52:25,410
and enjoyed having bibimbap.

752
00:52:25,410 --> 00:52:28,300
Could it have been the kids?

753
00:52:50,400 --> 00:52:52,840
Excuse me, what's going on here?

754
00:52:52,840 --> 00:52:54,440
What happened to the people that used to live here?

755
00:52:54,440 --> 00:52:57,020
I don't know. We're doing construction on it because it's an empty house.

756
00:52:57,020 --> 00:52:59,100
Excuse me? An empty house?

757
00:52:59,100 --> 00:53:02,480
Yes. No one lives here.

758
00:53:02,480 --> 00:53:04,270
Thank you.

759
00:53:09,430 --> 00:53:12,640
The number you have dialed is not in service.

760
00:53:12,640 --> 00:53:14,810
Please check the–

761
00:53:23,250 --> 00:53:24,680
Hello.

762
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:28,150
Has Ms. Jo Sarah come here recently by any chance?

763
00:53:28,150 --> 00:53:32,160
Ms. Jo Sarah? No, she hasn't.

764
00:53:32,160 --> 00:53:35,680
Ms. Sarah left this job a long time ago.

765
00:53:38,170 --> 00:53:40,040
Thank you.

766
00:53:41,670 --> 00:53:44,950
[Seoul Prison]

767
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:51,120
Thank you for the money.

768
00:53:51,120 --> 00:53:58,340
Mom... Why did you do it?

769
00:53:58,340 --> 00:54:04,870
I did stupid, dumb, idiotic things because I wanted to be with Se Jong,

770
00:54:04,870 --> 00:54:09,070
but why did you commit that?

771
00:54:09,070 --> 00:54:11,760
Because I was sorry.

772
00:54:14,160 --> 00:54:17,590
I did it because I was sorry.

773
00:54:17,590 --> 00:54:19,800
What?

774
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:22,070
What do you mean?

775
00:54:23,580 --> 00:54:27,220
You gave your youth to that family.

776
00:54:27,220 --> 00:54:30,880
But how could they just kick you out like that?

777
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:32,120
It was unfair.

778
00:54:32,120 --> 00:54:37,120
It was unfair, so unfair, that's why I did it!

779
00:54:38,870 --> 00:54:45,080
Mi Sook told us to move out right around that time,

780
00:54:45,080 --> 00:54:50,890
so... I went to Dae Ran.

781
00:54:50,890 --> 00:54:55,970
Dae Ran, who has a pile of gold in her safe,

782
00:54:55,970 --> 00:55:01,300
and I asked if she could lend me just 200 million won, but she said she has no such money.

783
00:55:01,300 --> 00:55:06,440
So I lost my mind.

784
00:55:06,440 --> 00:55:12,720
Sarah... I must've been possessed or something.

785
00:55:14,510 --> 00:55:17,390
I'm sorry, Sarah.

786
00:55:17,390 --> 00:55:20,370
I'm so sorry.

787
00:55:22,300 --> 00:55:25,020
Mom...

788
00:55:25,020 --> 00:55:31,970
I'm not going to come to see you anymore.

789
00:55:31,970 --> 00:55:34,390
Sarah...

790
00:55:34,390 --> 00:55:37,260
When you get out of here,

791
00:55:37,260 --> 00:55:42,500
you shouldn't look for me as well.

792
00:55:44,000 --> 00:55:48,100
Sarah, what are you saying?

793
00:55:48,100 --> 00:55:53,400
Mom, you're embarrassed by me,

794
00:55:53,400 --> 00:55:56,910
and I'm embarrassed by you.

795
00:55:56,910 --> 00:56:04,350
So you and I should live on our own.

796
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:13,390
I came for the last time to say this.

797
00:56:16,070 --> 00:56:18,810
I'm going to go now.

798
00:56:20,820 --> 00:56:23,660
Take care of your health.

799
00:56:28,450 --> 00:56:34,280
Sarah... Sarah...

800
00:56:34,280 --> 00:56:39,430
Sarah, I'm sorry...

801
00:56:39,430 --> 00:56:43,560
You're mom's sorry...

802
00:56:43,560 --> 00:56:50,060
I'm so sorry, Sarah...

803
00:56:50,060 --> 00:56:51,820
Sarah...

804
00:56:51,820 --> 00:56:55,990
I'm sorry...

805
00:56:58,060 --> 00:57:01,630
I did it wrong, Sarah...

806
00:57:53,990 --> 00:57:59,030
What do we do with Mi Rim?

807
00:57:59,030 --> 00:58:03,960
Mom, everything Joon Oh and Mi Rim said was right.

808
00:58:03,960 --> 00:58:08,200
Who are we to make a fuss when they're staying together because they like each other.

809
00:58:08,200 --> 00:58:12,990
That's what I think. They're not saying they'd get married right away either.

810
00:58:12,990 --> 00:58:15,200
I'm worried because of the in-law.

811
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:18,880
If they break up, Mi Rim is the only one who'd be affected.

812
00:58:18,880 --> 00:58:22,200
It's still a hard world for women.

813
00:58:22,200 --> 00:58:25,220
If I get reborn, I want to be born in France.

814
00:58:25,220 --> 00:58:29,150
There's no disadvantage for women even if people live together before marriage.

815
00:58:29,150 --> 00:58:32,100
Do you want to be reborn in the first place?

816
00:58:32,100 --> 00:58:36,050
But where did my husband go after leaving the store alone?

817
00:58:36,050 --> 00:58:38,800
Hey, where did your dad go?

818
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:43,190
He called a while ago and said he couldn't come because he had to take care of something.

819
00:58:43,190 --> 00:58:45,920
What does he have to take care of this early in the morning?

820
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:49,000
- Okay.
- I'm going on a delivery.

821
00:58:51,220 --> 00:58:54,240
He has kept leaving the store recently.

822
00:58:54,240 --> 00:58:57,690
Why is it so bugging me?

823
00:59:03,420 --> 00:59:04,620
The patient is done with the tests.

824
00:59:04,620 --> 00:59:06,720
Thank you.

825
00:59:26,740 --> 00:59:28,390
What is this?

826
00:59:28,390 --> 00:59:31,430
Ginger tea. Try it.

827
00:59:31,430 --> 00:59:36,920
It's good for the immune system. It should be tasty because I put some honey in it too.

828
00:59:41,420 --> 00:59:44,030
How is it?

829
00:59:44,030 --> 00:59:46,370
It's tasty.

830
00:59:47,530 --> 00:59:50,680
Don't think about giving up again, okay?

831
00:59:50,680 --> 00:59:55,670
The doctor also said that the patient's will is important.

832
00:59:55,670 --> 00:59:58,150
Be strong.

833
00:59:59,540 --> 01:00:03,280
Since you got tested today, you should get surgery if they say it's possible.

834
01:00:03,280 --> 01:00:04,900
Okay?

835
01:00:04,900 --> 01:00:07,090
Okay.

836
01:00:08,560 --> 01:00:11,830
You have to eat well to get through surgery.

837
01:00:11,830 --> 01:00:18,480
I'll stay beside you until the end like last time, so trust me and do as I say.

838
01:00:18,480 --> 01:00:23,090
But what if your wife finds out about this?

839
01:00:23,090 --> 01:00:26,350
She won't just sit back.

840
01:00:26,350 --> 01:00:30,150
I'll take care of it, so don't worry.

841
01:00:30,150 --> 01:00:33,780
She'll understand if she finds out you're sick.

842
01:00:33,780 --> 01:00:36,320
She's not a harsh person.

843
01:00:37,910 --> 01:00:40,340
Drink some more.

844
01:00:50,340 --> 01:00:52,290
Yes, Se Chan.

845
01:00:52,290 --> 01:00:56,060
Ms. Park. I'm so upset.

846
01:00:56,060 --> 01:00:58,310
Why? What's wrong?

847
01:00:58,310 --> 01:01:03,160
I think my dad has a new girlfriend.

848
01:01:03,230 --> 01:01:04,440
What?

849
01:01:04,440 --> 01:01:10,350
I thought you'd be back because you came to interview for the job,

850
01:01:10,350 --> 01:01:14,040
but my dad said you wouldn't come back.

851
01:01:14,040 --> 01:01:19,500
I think it's because my dad has a new girlfriend.

852
01:01:19,500 --> 01:01:25,470
He said he's going to introduce us to his new girlfriend at the pasta place we went to last time,

853
01:01:25,470 --> 01:01:29,300
but I really don't want to go.

854
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:35,520
Even if my dad gets a new girlfriend and we get a new teacher,

855
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:38,480
I'll never forget you.

856
01:01:38,480 --> 01:01:41,630
I won't betray you.

857
01:01:44,600 --> 01:01:48,520
Okay. Thank you, Se Chan.

858
01:01:48,520 --> 01:01:55,250
Ms. Park, even if it's just us, can you meet outside with Se Jong and me?

859
01:01:55,250 --> 01:01:58,660
Okay. Let's do that.

860
01:02:08,700 --> 01:02:11,980
Say hello when she arrives, okay?

861
01:02:28,490 --> 01:02:32,550
Welcome. This is Ms. An Ji Min.

862
01:02:32,550 --> 01:02:34,700
Hello, kids.

863
01:02:36,130 --> 01:02:38,150
This is Lee Jenny, my oldest daughter,

864
01:02:38,150 --> 01:02:41,530
Lee Se Chan, the middle child, and the youngest, Lee Se Jong.

865
01:02:41,530 --> 01:02:43,660
Kids, say hello.

866
01:02:43,660 --> 01:02:45,210
Hello.

867
01:02:45,210 --> 01:02:47,570
Nice to meet you.

868
01:02:54,020 --> 01:02:57,450
I ordered what the kids like first.

869
01:02:57,450 --> 01:02:59,690
Okay, that's good.

870
01:03:01,760 --> 01:03:06,920
Dad, let's cheers to celebrate this meeting.

871
01:03:06,920 --> 01:03:10,310
Shall we?

872
01:03:10,310 --> 01:03:13,390
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

873
01:03:22,140 --> 01:03:24,250
Why don't you try some food?

874
01:03:28,110 --> 01:03:29,640
How old are you?

875
01:03:29,640 --> 01:03:31,730
I'm twelve.

876
01:03:34,200 --> 01:03:36,730
Excuse me for a moment.

877
01:04:07,980 --> 01:04:11,280
Dad, where did you go?

878
01:04:11,280 --> 01:04:16,940
I had something urgent to take care of, so I was on the phone for a moment.

879
01:04:18,710 --> 01:04:21,750
Your kids are very quiet and well-behaved.

880
01:04:21,750 --> 01:04:24,110
They are at the age to be mischievous.

881
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:27,680
It's not because you don't like me, is it?

882
01:04:27,680 --> 01:04:32,220
I worked really hard on my style today before I left.

883
01:04:32,240 --> 01:04:35,500
It's not that. They're just shy.

884
01:04:35,500 --> 01:04:37,370
Right?

885
01:04:49,020 --> 01:04:51,330
Did the kids get home safe?

886
01:04:51,330 --> 01:04:54,780
Yes. I just came back from dropping them off at home.

887
01:04:56,310 --> 01:04:59,130
You had something to say?

888
01:05:02,670 --> 01:05:07,530
Ji Min, I actually have someone I used to like,

889
01:05:07,530 --> 01:05:10,260
and I don't think I'm done with those feelings.

890
01:05:10,260 --> 01:05:14,220
I don't think it's right to go out with you in this state.

891
01:05:16,600 --> 01:05:19,460
I'm sorry, Ji Min.

892
01:05:22,740 --> 01:05:28,750
I'm a little relieved to hear you saying that.

893
01:05:28,750 --> 01:05:32,530
To be honest, I was a little surprised when I saw the kids.

894
01:05:32,530 --> 01:05:36,430
I knew you had three kids, of course,

895
01:05:36,430 --> 01:05:42,380
but seeing them there in real life was different from thinking about them.

896
01:05:42,380 --> 01:05:49,310
So I was about to tell you I'm not confident about it either.

897
01:05:49,310 --> 01:05:52,660
Is that so?

898
01:05:52,660 --> 01:05:58,900
But I feel less guilty because of what you said.

899
01:05:58,900 --> 01:06:00,950
You don't have to feel guilty.

900
01:06:00,950 --> 01:06:04,490
It was good to see you anyway, Ji Min.

901
01:06:04,490 --> 01:06:05,940
Me, too.

902
01:06:05,940 --> 01:06:10,170
I hope you meet someone good.

903
01:06:10,170 --> 01:06:12,790
Thank you.

904
01:06:51,930 --> 01:06:55,570
Do you know what you did when you came to our house?

905
01:06:55,570 --> 01:07:02,560
Se Chan and Se Jong just barely got used to being without you.

906
01:07:02,560 --> 01:07:07,480
But because you suddenly came by and stirred them up, my children are having a hard time again.

907
01:07:07,480 --> 01:07:12,340
Se Jong's separation anxiety just got settled. Why would you act this way?

908
01:07:12,340 --> 01:07:14,740
Cheers.

909
01:08:01,350 --> 01:08:03,510
It's me.

910
01:08:05,920 --> 01:08:12,750
I'm coming for the last time because I have something to say to you.

911
01:08:14,570 --> 01:08:17,250
Go ahead.

912
01:08:17,250 --> 01:08:25,320
Chairman, you said you wanted to break up with me

913
01:08:25,320 --> 01:08:28,820
because you felt guilty for me suffering and getting hurt

914
01:08:28,820 --> 01:08:32,150
due to the fact that I was going out with you.

915
01:08:32,150 --> 01:08:36,480
You told me to meet someone that's blessed by everyone.

916
01:08:36,480 --> 01:08:42,280
But what you said was wrong.

917
01:08:42,280 --> 01:08:47,630
No matter what pain and suffering came to me,

918
01:08:47,630 --> 01:08:51,320
even if people pointed at and judged me,

919
01:08:51,320 --> 01:08:56,120
I was happy because I was beside you.

920
01:08:56,120 --> 01:09:01,840
And I wasn't scared because you were beside me.

921
01:09:01,840 --> 01:09:08,100
So until now, I didn't think any of that was a struggle.

922
01:09:12,760 --> 01:09:14,210
Ms. Park...

923
01:09:14,210 --> 01:09:19,350
But Chairman, do you know that?

924
01:09:19,350 --> 01:09:27,230
The person who hurt me the most was you.

925
01:09:27,230 --> 01:09:37,900
The person who hurt me the most is no one else and nothing else but you.

926
01:09:37,900 --> 01:09:42,650
About me, or my feelings,

927
01:09:42,650 --> 01:09:45,500
you don't know anything about it.

928
01:09:45,500 --> 01:09:50,110
Because of you acting like that,

929
01:09:50,110 --> 01:09:55,190
it feels like my heart is getting ripped out.

930
01:09:55,190 --> 01:09:59,280
♫ It makes me cry  ♫

931
01:09:59,280 --> 01:10:05,220
You're the person who made me hurt like this, and I don't like that person anymore.

932
01:10:05,220 --> 01:10:06,980
Goodbye.

933
01:10:06,980 --> 01:10:09,710
♫ It reminds me of that person's touch ♫

934
01:10:09,710 --> 01:10:17,430
♫ I couldn't hold her and just trembled my heart ♫

935
01:10:17,430 --> 01:10:24,080
♫ My beautiful love ♫

936
01:10:24,080 --> 01:10:31,260
♫ It seems like love is bitter ♫

937
01:10:31,260 --> 01:10:34,770
If we get together again, everything will be repeated again.

938
01:10:34,770 --> 01:10:38,250
People's prejudice, your father's disapproval.

939
01:10:38,250 --> 01:10:44,260
Jenny's opposition. There is nothing but wound for us.

940
01:10:44,260 --> 01:10:48,790
Even so, I want to be with you.

941
01:10:48,790 --> 01:10:53,150
♫ My unforgettable love ♫

942
01:10:53,150 --> 01:10:55,020
♫ Why do you run away, love ♫

943
01:10:55,020 --> 01:11:05,450
The person who hurt me the most is no one else and nothing else but you.

944
01:11:05,450 --> 01:11:10,040
About me, or my feelings,

945
01:11:10,040 --> 01:11:12,960
you don't know anything about it.

946
01:11:12,960 --> 01:11:19,320
Because of you acting like that, it feels like my heart is getting ripped out.

947
01:11:19,320 --> 01:11:25,460
You're the person who made me hurt like this, and I don't like that person anymore.

948
01:11:36,710 --> 01:11:44,310
♫ Why do you run away, love. Like a shy child ♫

949
01:11:44,310 --> 01:11:51,140
♫ In case I lose it, I hold it tight ♫

950
01:11:51,140 --> 01:11:58,310
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

951
01:11:58,310 --> 01:12:05,050
♫It would be nice to take a break♫

952
01:12:05,050 --> 01:12:13,020
♫ I have to abandon the longing and the grieves ♫

953
01:12:13,020 --> 01:12:15,530
♫ What am I looking for on this road wandering ♫

954
01:12:15,530 --> 01:12:18,520
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

955
01:12:18,520 --> 01:12:21,680
Why is my dad making it so difficult by liking Ms. Park when everyone is against her?

956
01:12:21,680 --> 01:12:26,290
Your dad has three children. It'll be hard to find someone who'd like your dad for who he is.

957
01:12:26,290 --> 01:12:28,000
Ajussi, what are you doing?

958
01:12:28,000 --> 01:12:29,710
Take it, I said! I'm not a beggar!

959
01:12:29,710 --> 01:12:31,310
You're pregnant right now, Sarah.

960
01:12:31,310 --> 01:12:34,360
I don't want to receive something like this from you.

961
01:12:34,360 --> 01:12:35,490
Where's your dad?

962
01:12:35,490 --> 01:12:37,650
Dad said he'd be late because he had something to take care of.

963
01:12:37,650 --> 01:12:40,330
Did that woman actually not go to the US?

964
01:12:40,330 --> 01:12:43,820
Why are they together? Are they back together?

965
01:12:43,820 --> 01:12:47,730
I'm so hungry. I wonder what there will be today.

966
01:12:47,730 --> 01:12:50,430
It's not a ghost. It's me, me!

967
01:12:50,430 --> 01:12:54,540
I rushed because I was scared that you might run away from me.

968
01:12:54,540 --> 01:12:57,540
No matter what happens, let's never break up again.

969
01:12:57,540 --> 01:13:02,000
Chairman!
[Park Dan Dan! Please accept my love!]
